column1: Will Barnaby Joyce win the upcoming by-election in New England, Australia?
column11: Australia's former Deputy Prime Minister Barnaby Joyce is running in a by-election scheduled for 2 December 2017, a race which may determine which party holds the majority in Australia's House of Representatives (NY Times, Northern Daily Leader). Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: New England by-election: 'Landslide' win expected for Joyce as polls open
He seems pretty favourite to win by all accounts but he is facing 16 candidates.
Won in the past, still popular so likely to win.
When this election has upcome (and presumably downgone), Joyce will have won.
